Over the summer, a lot of seaweed washed on shore at our local beach. Plastic at sea gets tangled in seaweed and comes with it. @kelseyoanderson & I spent a short time cleaning as best we could on 100 yards of beach. What we found was unfortunately what we have come to expect. Over 100 bottle tops, over 50 plastic straws and countless other pieces of indiscriminate plastics. This is a real problem that needs addressing. RRR: - Reduce/eliminate single use plastics as much you can. #passonplastic - Reuse plastics that are â€˜safeâ€™ - Recycle as much as you can (make sure to follow your local recycling guidelines. Unfortunately not all plastics are recyclable)
